WEBVTT

00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:06.000
PydyTuesday is a collaborative initiative linked with the TidyTuesday data project

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:11.440
that helps you grow your Python skills by analyzing a new dataset each week and sharing

00:00:11.440 --> 00:00:17.760
your discoveries. It's an ideal environment to learn Python, try out new Python tools,

00:00:17.760 --> 00:00:22.959
and connect with others. If you've been looking for an engaging way to expand your data science

00:00:22.959 --> 00:00:28.959
toolbox with fresh data and explore endless research questions, then PydyTuesday is for you!

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:35.759
So how do you get started with PydyTuesday? The best place to start is to visit the TidyTuesday

00:00:35.759 --> 00:00:42.799
GitHub repository and explore the various datasets. Beginning on February 18th, 2025,

00:00:42.799 --> 00:00:48.720
all future datasets include information for how to download the data using not just R,

00:00:48.720 --> 00:00:55.279
but also Python. For example, here is a dataset on the water quality at Sydney beaches.

00:00:55.759 --> 00:01:01.279
If we click on the title of the dataset, we will see the information for how to download the data

00:01:01.279 --> 00:01:05.599
using the PydyTuesday package or directly from the GitHub repository.

00:01:06.400 --> 00:01:12.000
PydyTuesday encourages the community to get creative with data. Feel free to build anything

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:18.160
you can imagine, a basic plot, an informative table, or even a sophisticated model using a new

00:01:18.160 --> 00:01:24.080
Python library. By sharing your creations on social media, you'll not only receive constructive

00:01:24.080 --> 00:01:29.760
feedback, but also inspire and educate fellow Python enthusiasts. If you're ready to level

00:01:29.760 --> 00:01:34.480
up your Python skills, then get started with PydyTuesday today and have fun!

